SIMPLE: nigh
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nigh
<hw>Nigh</hw> <pr>(n⟦imac⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Nigher</adjf>
<pr>(n⟦imac⟧"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos> <adjf>Nighest</adjf>, or
<adjf>Next</adjf> <pr>(n⟦ecr⟧kst)</pr>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>nigh</ets>, <ets>neigh</ets>, <ets>neih</ets>, AS.
<ets>ne⟦aacute⟧h</ets>, <ets>n⟦emac⟧h</ets>; akin to D. <ets>na</ets>,
adv., OS. <ets>n⟦amac⟧h</ets>, a., OHG. <ets>n⟦amac⟧h</ets>, G.
<ets>nah</ets>, a., <ets>nach</ets> to, after, Icel. <ets>n⟦amac⟧</ets>
(in comp.) nigh, Goth. <ets>n⟦emac⟧hw</ets>, <ets>n⟦emac⟧hwa</ets>,
adv., nigh. Cf. <er>Near</er>, <er>Neighbor</er>, <er>Next</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Not distant or remote in place or time; near.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The loud tumult shows the battle <qex>nigh</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not remote in degree, kindred, circumstances, etc.;
closely allied; intimate.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Nigh</xex> kinsmen.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Knolles.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ye . . . are made <qex>nigh</qex> by the blood of Christ.</q>
<rj><qau>Eph. ii. 13.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Near; close; adjacent; contiguous; present;
neighboring.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nigh</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nigh
<hw>Nigh</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>ne⟦aacute⟧h</ets>,
<ets>n⟦emac⟧h</ets>. See <er>Nigh</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>In a situation near in place or time, or in the course of events;
near.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He was sick, <qex>nigh</qex> unto death.</q> <rj><qau>Phil. ii.
27.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He drew not <qex>nigh</qex> unheard; the angel bright,⟦br⟧
Ere he drew <qex>nigh</qex>, his radiant visage turned.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Almost; nearly; <as>as, he was <ex>nigh</ex>
dead</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nigh</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Nigh
<hw>Nigh</hw>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <def>To draw nigh (to); to
approach; to come near.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Wyclif (Matt.
iii. 2).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nigh</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Nigh
<hw>Nigh</hw>, <pos>prep.</pos> <def>Near to; not remote or distant
from.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧was not this <xex>nigh</xex> shore?⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nighly</ent>⟦br⟧
